        "name": "Warg",
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "Warg Legends",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 341",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 341",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 341,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Wargs are the subject of many grim tales and campfire stories. Frightening accounts of wargs gobbling up children whole have a disturbing basis in fact, for these ravenous creatures have jaws that can unhinge like those of a serpent to gulp down small prey while the victim yet lives.",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "1.1",
              "aonid": 221,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "1.1",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Monster Core pg. 341",
              "aonid": 221,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Monster Core pg. 341",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Monster Core",
            "page": 341,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "The warg is an intelligent and malevolent wolf that dwells among goblins, hobgoblins, orcs, and violent humanoids.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
